data.description:
Odaily Planet Daily News Abstract contributor cygaar published a post on the X platform in response to some Abstract users being attacked: 
1. The relevant issue is related to Cardex. If you have ever interacted with this application, please revoke the relevant Session; 
2. It is not an AGW contract problem. There is no vulnerability in the wallet function. This specific problem is related to the application's negligence in session key management; 
3. If you have never interacted with cardex, your funds are safe; 
4. The contract has been audited many times, and the session key module has been specially reviewed. The relevant report will be released soon.
